 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 8:26:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue's vs paladins</span><hr size=1> A lot of people at high lvl will have enough mr that the small mr debuff on the proc (tashan right?) wont be enough.  In addition cure potions or cure spells will get rid of it.  <br>
<br>
Ridding yourself of tash may not help much vs a chanter since it takes almost no time to cast and costs a trivial amount of manna but it could be a lot more helpful when your foe has to actually proc it.<br>
<br>
Also you should take quite a lot of dmg in the time your jousting with your 9 dmg weapon )).<br>
<br>
I personally wouldn't bother on a pvp server at high lvl unless you know your target has fairly bad mr to start with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 8:46:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue's vs paladins</span><hr size=1> At high level, with a strong 2handed weapon to joust, plus their dot heal, paladins are a very difficult foe to face one-on-one.<br>
